23F2\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary report:\\n\\n## Comprehensive Report: Metadata Fetching During Resume/Rewind Operations\\n\\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the codebase to understand how metadata is fetched during resume/rewind operations. Here are my findings:\\n\\n### 1. **Git Fetch Operations for Metadata Branch**\\n\\nThe codebase uses **explicit git fetch operations** (via CLI, not go-git) to ensure credential helper support and authentication compatibility:\\n\\n**File:** `/home/coder/git/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/git_operations.go`\\n\\n**Function: `FetchMetadataBranch()`** (lines 357-396)\\n- Uses `git fetch origin +refs/heads/entire/checkpoints/v1:refs/remotes/origin/entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- Explicitly avoids go-git for fetch because go-git doesn't support credential helpers\\n- Creates/updates local branch from remote-tracking ref after fetch\\n- 2-minute timeout context\\n\\n**Function: `FetchAndCheckoutRemoteBranch()`** (lines 312-355)\\n- Similar pattern for fetching user feature branches\\n- Used by `entire resume` when branch exists on remote but not locally\\n\\n### 2. **How `GetSessionLog` and `GetSessionInfo` Work**\\n\\n**File:** `/home/coder/git/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_logs.go`\\n\\n**GetSessionInfo()** (lines 25-65)\\n- Finds sessions for the current HEAD commit\\n- Returns `SessionInfo` with SessionID and shadow branch reference\\n\\n**GetCheckpointLog()** (lines 98-103)\\n- Calls `s.getCheckpointLog(ctx, checkpoint.CheckpointID)` for committed checkpoints\\n- Delegates to checkpoint store to read from `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n\\n**GetSessionMetadataRef()** (lines 76-94)\\n- Returns reference to most recent metadata commit on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- Format: `entire/checkpoints/v1:<commit-hash>`\\n\\n### 3. **How Rewind Reads Checkpoint Data**\\n\\n**File:** `/home/coder/gi