dBlobFetch`** — After treeless fetch, read a `full.jsonl` via `BlobResolver`. Verify the blob is fetched on demand and content is correct.\\n\\n7. **`TestSparseFetch_SkipsLocalBlobs`** — Do a full fetch first (all blobs local). Then do treeless fetch. Verify `ReadBlob` uses the go-git fast path (no git CLI needed).\\n\\n8. **`TestSparseFetch_MultiSession`** — Checkpoint with 3 sessions. Treeless fetch. Read all sessions via sparse path. Verify all 3 `full.jsonl` blobs are fetched.\\n\\n9. **`TestRestoreLogsOnly_Sparse`** — End-to-end: push metadata to local bare remote, treeless fetch, `RestoreLogsOnly`. Verify transcripts are restored correctly.\\n\\n### Files Changed\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `checkpoint/blob_resolver.go` | **New** — `BlobResolver` struct |\\n| `checkpoint/blob_resolver_test.go` | **New** — Unit tests for `BlobResolver` |\\n| `checkpoint/committed.go` | Add `ReadSessionContentSparse()` |\\n| `checkpoint/committed_test.go` | Tests for sparse reading |\\n| `git_operations.go` | Add `FetchMetadataTreeOnly()`, add `ConfigurePromisorRemote()` |\\n| `resume.go` | Update `getMetadataTree()` to try treeless fetch first |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` | Update `RestoreLogsOnly()` to use `BlobResolver` |\\n\\n### Migration / Backward Compatibility\\n\\n- **No breaking changes**: `FetchMetadataBranch()` (full fetch) remains as fallback\\n- **Graceful degradation**: If `--filter=blob:none` fails (old git server), falls back to full fetch\\n- **Config is additive**: Setting `remote.origin.promisor=true` doesn't affect normal git operations — it only activates when an object is missing from a promisor pack\\n- **go-git reads still work**: If all blobs are already local (from a previous full fetch), `BlobResolver` uses the go-git fast path with zero overhead\\n\\n### Edge Cases\\n\\n1. **Old git version** (< 2.19, no partial clone): `--filter` flag fails → fall back to `FetchMetadataBranch()`\\n2. **No remote configured**: Skip prom