        │ • tree.Tree(\\\"0/\\\")      │\\n    │   --filter=blob:none│            │ • tree.FindEntry(path) │\\n    │                     │            │   → TreeEntry{Hash}    │\\n    │ Phase 2: fetch      │            │ • HasEncodedObject(h)  │\\n    │   specific blobs    │            │ • BlobObject(h)        │\\n    └─────────────────────┘            └────────────────────────┘\\n```\\n\\n### Flow\\n\\n1. **`git fetch --filter=blob:none`** (CLI) — downloads commits + trees only\\n2. **go-git tree walking** — navigate to checkpoint dir, enumerate sessions using `tree.Tree()` and `FindEntry()`. These only read tree objects (local). `FindEntry` returns `TreeEntry.Hash` — the blob hash — without fetching the blob.\\n3. **go-git `HasEncodedObject(hash)`** — for each `full.jsonl` blob hash, check if it's already in the local object store. Fast: checks loose objects + packfile indices, no I/O.\\n4. **`git fetch-pack <url> <hash> ...`** (CLI) — for each **missing** blob, fetch just those objects. With protocol v2 and `allow-reachable-sha1-in-want` (GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket all support this), individual object hashes can be requested. If a blob is already local, skip it.\\n5. **go-git `BlobObject(hash)`** — read the now-local blob content.\\n\\n### Why `fetch-pack` for specific blobs\\n\\n`git fetch-pack` is the plumbing command behind `git fetch`. Unlike `git fetch` (which takes refspecs), `fetch-pack` can request specific objects by hash when the server advertises `allow-reachable-sha1-in-want` (standard since Git 2.11, all major hosts support it). This is how we avoid fetching **all** blobs when we only need a few `full.jsonl` files:\\n\\n```bash\\nurl=$(git remote get-url origin)\\ngit fetch-pack --thin --no-progress \\\"$url\\\" <hash1> <hash2> <hash3>\\n```\\n\\n**Fallback**: If `fetch-pack` by hash fails (old server, no `allow-reachable-sha1-in-want`), fall back to a full unfiltered `git fetch` of the metadata ref. Pack negotiation ensures only blobs are transferred since commits + trees are already local.\\n\\n### Detailed Design\\n\\n#### 1. `checkpoint/blob_resolver.go` — Local object store wrapper\\n\\n```go\\n// BlobResolver checks blob existence and reads blobs from go-git's local\\n// object store (loose objects + packfiles). No remote operations.\\ntype BlobResolver struct {\\n    storer storer.EncodedObjectStorer\\n}\\n\\n// HasBlob returns true if the blob exists in the local object store.\\nfunc (r *BlobResolver) HasBlob(hash plumbing.Hash) bool\\n\\n// ReadBlob reads blob content from the local store.\\n// Returns plumbing.ErrObjectNotFound if not local.\\nfunc (r *BlobResolver) ReadBlob(hash plumbing.Hash) ([]byte, error)\\n```\\n\\n#### 2. `checkpoint/committed.go` — Tree walking without blob reads\\n\\n```go\\n// TranscriptBlobRef identifies a transcript blob within a checkpoint tree.\\ntype TranscriptBlobRef struct {\\n    SessionIndex int\\n    BlobHash     plumbing.Hash\\n    Path         string // relative to checkpoint dir, e.g. \\\"0/full.jsonl\\\"\\n}\\n\\n// CollectTranscriptBlobHashes walks the checkpoint tree and returns blob\\n// hashes for all full.jsonl files (including chunks) and metadata.json files.\\n// Only reads tree objects — works after a treeless fetch.\\nfunc (s *GitStore) CollectTranscriptBlobHashes(\\n    ctx context.Context,\\n    checkpointID id.CheckpointID,\\n) ([]TranscriptBlobRef, error) {\\n    // Navigate: tree → <id[:2]> → <id[2:]> (all tree reads)\\n    // For each session subdir (0, 1, 2, ...):\\n    //   FindEntry(\\\"full.jsonl\\\") → TreeEntry{Hash}    (no blob read)\\n    //   FindEntry(\\\"full.jsonl.0\\\"), .1, etc. for chunks\\n    //   FindEntry(\\\"metadata.json\\\") → for session metadata\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### 3. `git_operations.go` — Remote fetch operations\\n\\n```go\\n// FetchMetadataTreeOnly fetches the metadata branch with --filter=blob:none.\\n// Only commit and tree objects are downloaded.\\nfunc FetchMetadataTreeOnly(ctx context.Context) error {\\n    // git fetch --filter=blob:none origin +refs/heads/entire/checkpoints/v1:...\\n    // Then update local branch ref (same pattern as FetchMetadataBranch)\\n}\\n\\n// FetchBlobsByHash fetches specific blob objects from the remote by hash.\\n// Uses git fetch-pack with individual object hashes.\\n// Falls back to full metadata branch fetch if fetch-pack fails.\\nfunc FetchBlobsByHash(ctx context.Context, hashes []plumbing.Hash) error {\\n    // Get remote URL\\n    // git fetch-pack --thin --no-progress <url> <hash1> <hash2> ...\\n    // Fallback: git fetch origin +refs/heads/entire/checkpoints/v1:...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### 4. `resume.go` — Updated flow\\n\\n```go\\nfunc getMetadataTree(ctx context.Context, repo *git.Repository) (*object.Tree, error) {\\n    // 1. Try local branch\\n    // 2. Treeless fetch via FetchMetadataTreeOnly()\\n    // 3. Fallback: full fetch via FetchMetadataBranch()\\n}\\n\\n// ensureTranscriptBlobs checks which transcript blobs are local and\\n// fetches any missing ones from the remote.\\nfunc ensureTranscriptBlobs(ctx context.Context, repo *git.Repository, cpID id.CheckpointID) error {\\n    store := checkpoint.NewGitStore(repo)\\n    refs, _ := store.CollectTranscriptBlobHashes(ctx, cpID)\\n\\n    resolver := checkpoint.NewBlobResolver(repo.Storer)\\n    var missing []plumbing.Hash\\n    for _, ref := range refs {\\n        if !resolver.HasBlob(ref.BlobHash) {\\n            missing = append(missing, ref.BlobHash)\\n        }\\n    }\\n    if len(missing) == 0 {\\n        return nil // all blobs already local\\n    }\\n    return FetchBlobsByHash(ctx, missing)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Test Plan\\n\\nAll tests use local bare repos as remotes — no network, no auth.\\n\\n**Unit tests (go-git store, no remote):**\\n\\n| Test | Verifies |\\n|------|----------|\\n| `TestBlobResolver_HasBlob_Present` | Returns true for blob in packfile |\\n| `TestBlobResolver_HasBlob_Missing` | Returns false for absent hash |\\n| `TestBlobResolver_ReadBlob` | Reads correct content from store |\\n| `TestCollectTranscriptBlobHashes_SingleSession` | Finds `0/full.jsonl` blob hash via `FindEntry` |\\n| `TestCollectTranscriptBlobHashes_MultiSession` | Finds blob hashes for sessions 0, 1, 2 |\\n| `TestCollectTranscriptBlobHashes_ChunkedTranscript` | Finds `full.jsonl.0`, `.1`, etc. |\\n\\n**Integration tests (local bare remote):**\\n\\n| Test | Verifies |\\n|------|----------|\\n| `TestTreelessFetch_TreesLocalBlobsMissing` | After `--filter=blob:none`, `FindEntry` works but `HasEncodedObject` returns not-found for blobs |\\n| `TestFetchBlobsByHash` | After treeless fetch, `FetchBlobsByHash` fetches specific blobs, then `HasEncodedObject` returns nil |\\n| `TestFetchBlobsByHash_SkipsLocalBlobs` | Blobs already local → not re-fetched |\\n| `TestFetchBlobsByHash_Fallback` | If `fetch-pack` fails, falls back to full fetch |\\n| `TestEnsureTranscriptBlobs_EndToEnd` | Full flow: treeless fetch → collect hashes → check local → fetch missing → read content |\\n\\n**Test setup:**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc setupTreelessFetchTest(t *testing.T) (localRepo, bareRepo) {\\n    // 1. Create bare repo with metadata branch containing checkpoint data\\n    // 2. Create local repo with remote pointing to bare repo\\n    // 3. Do NOT fetch yet — caller controls fetch strategy\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Files Changed\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `checkpoint/blob_resolver.go` | **New** — local object store wrapper |\\n| `checkpoint/blob_resolver_test.go` | **New** — unit tests |\\n| `checkpoint/committed.go` | Add `CollectTranscriptBlobHashes()`, `TranscriptBlobRef` |\\n| `checkpoint/committed_test.go` | Tests for blob hash collection |\\n| `git_operations.go` | Add `FetchMetadataTreeOnly()`, `FetchBlobsByHash()` |\\n| `git_operations_test.go` | Integration tests with local bare remote |\\n| `resume.go` | Update `getMetadataTree()`, add `ensureTranscriptBlobs()` |\\n\\n### Edge Cases\\n\\n1. **`fetch-pack` by hash fails** (old server): Fall back to full `git fetch` of the ref\\n2. **All blobs already local** (repeat resume): `HasEncodedObject` → all nil → skip fetch entirely\\n3. **Chunked transcripts**: `CollectTranscriptBlobHashes` iterates `full.jsonl.0`, `.1`, etc.\\n4. **No remote**: Skip remote ops, only check local store\\n5. **`--filter` not supported by server**: `FetchMetadataTreeOnly` fails → fall back to `FetchMetadataBranch`\\n\\n---\\n\\nWant me to proceed with implementation?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":105,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":99729,\"output_tokens\":2699,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":105,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYwDRoPP2TWdyRJHsr8Zz\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"832e69ab-c064-47fa-9e4b-6a52afea9c85\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T11:30:07.314Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"832e69ab-c064-47fa-9e4b-6a52afea9c85\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/home/coder/git/entireio/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3261e1c6-a0db-489e-8d99-ad60228e4158\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"pjbgf/jsonl-data2\",\"slug\":\"reactive-dancing-wolf\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"2514fd09-8481-4682-92af-dcbbb7b18e5a\",\"toolUseID\":\"2514fd09-8481-4682-92af-dcbbb7b18e5a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T11:30:07.469Z\",\"uuid\":\"89edf02f-97e5-48a4-930c-b5a8ac3c1a5c\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"89edf02f-97e5-48a4-930c-b5a8ac3c1a5c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/home/coder/git/entireio/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3261e1c6-a0db-489e-8d99-ad60228e4158\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"pjbgf/jsonl-data2\",\"slug\":\"re